cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with resource allocation in data centers, which involves networking and communication between different components. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely category as the paper deals with data center resource allocation and management. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a temperature-aware scheme to manage the cooling system and IT equipment lifespan in data centers. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with optimizing the power consumption of IT equipment in data centers. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper proposes a scheme to improve the performance of data center resource allocation by avoiding hot spots and reducing power consumption.
